  86:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ================================================
ARM GAS  C:\Users\bku598\AppData\Local\Temp\cczRNjh6.s 			page 3


  87:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  88:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) RTC frequency can be digitally calibrated with a resolution of about
  89:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         0.954 ppm with a range from -487.1 ppm to +488.5 ppm.
  90:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         The correction of the frequency is performed using a series of small
  91:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         adjustments (adding and/or subtracting individual RTCCLK pulses).
  92:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) The smooth digital calibration is performed during a cycle of about 2^20
  93:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         RTCCLK pulses (or 32 seconds) when the input frequency is 32,768 Hz.
  94:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         This cycle is maintained by a 20-bit counter clocked by RTCCLK.
  95:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) The smooth calibration register (RTC_CALR) specifies the number of RTCCLK
  96:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         clock cycles to be masked during the 32-second cycle.
  97:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To configure the RTC Smooth Digital Calibration value and the corresponding
  98:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         calibration cycle period (32s,16s and 8s) use the HAL_RTCEx_SetSmoothCalib()
  99:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         function.
 100:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
 101:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** Outputs configuration ***
 102:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   =============================
 103:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..] The RTC has 2 different outputs:
 104:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) RTC_ALARM: this output is used to manage the RTC alarms (Alarm A and Alarm B)
 105:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         and WaKeUp signals.
 106:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         To output the selected RTC signal, use the HAL_RTC_Init() function.
 107:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) RTC_CALIB: this output is 512Hz signal or 1Hz.
 108:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         To enable the RTC_CALIB, use the HAL_RTCEx_SetCalibrationOutPut() function.
 109:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) Two pins can be used as RTC_ALARM or RTC_CALIB output, selected through
 110:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         bit OUT_RMP of the RTC_OR register:
 111:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) When the RTC_CALIB or RTC_ALARM output is selected, the RTC_OUT pin is
 112:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         automatically configured in output alternate function.
 113:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
 114:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   @endverbatim
 115:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ******************************************************************************
